               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-275-person2554">
                  JOHN 
                  SIMPSON
               <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2554" type="surname" value="SIMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2554" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2554" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18200918-275-viclabel1578" type="occupation">jeweller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-275-victim2553 t18200918-275-viclabel1578"></join>, and live in Middle-row, Holborn. On the 4th of July I was in <placeName id="t18200918-275-crimeloc1579">Covent Garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-275-crimeloc1579" type="placeName" value="Covent Garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-275-crimeloc1579" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-275-off1576 t18200918-275-crimeloc1579"></join>; a man touched me on the shoulder, and asked if I had lost my handkerchief; I felt and missed it. The prisoner was about one hundred yards off with a companion - we secured him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-275-person2555">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COLTON
               <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2555" type="surname" value="COLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2555" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2555" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a broker, and live at Battle-bridge. On the day of the Westminster meeting I was at Covent Garden, and saw the prosecutor standing by a man who was selling a composition, and saw the prisoner with two more try several gentlemens' pockets. I saw him try Simpson's pocket, then go away and bring two more; then saw him take the handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket. I asked him if he had lost anything - he said he had. When they saw me touch the prosecutor, two went one way, and the other another. I seized the prisoner, but did not find the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-275-person2556">
                  WILLIAM 
                  LEE
               <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2556" type="surname" value="LEE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2556" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-275-person2556" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Bow-street patrol. They were given into my charge - the one was discharged.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. My mother left me in the market; the gentleman went by and took me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200918-275-verdict1580" type="verdictDescription">
